 DO YOU GET ON WITH THE STUDENTS?.     THERE ARE OVER 34,000 STUDENTS AT BONN UNIVERSITY, 60% OF WHOM LIVE IN THETOWN, SO THAT THEIR NEEDS MUST BE CATERED FOR BY BONN PUBLIC LIBRARIES.STUDENTS FROM COLOGNE AND AACHEN UNIVERSITIES ALSO MAKE USE OF BONN'S LIBRARYSERVICES. IF A STUDENT CANNOT FIND THE REQUIRED MATERIAL IN THE UNIVERSITYLIBRARY HE TURNS TO THE PUBLIC LIBRARY FOR HELP. IN THE PUBLIC LIBRARY HEFINDS THE ADVANTAGES OF LONG OPENING HOURS AND OF ALL MEDIA ON OPEN ACCESS. IN1980 15.73% OF ALL LOANS IN BONN PUBLIC LIBRARIES WERE MADE TO UNIVERSITYSTUDENTS; THEY USED MAINLY ACADEMIC MATERIAL, ESPECIALLY SOCIOLOGY. THE STATEPROVIDES 13.1% OF TOTAL LIBRARY FUNDS FOR SPECIALISED MATERIAL